The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically chordal graphs and their tree models. The paper also discusses computational complexity and algorithms for calculating certain properties of these graphs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
